you said you were going and didnn't call me.

that I placed the paperwork down and when I left I didn't have the paperwork in my hands. Are you in the
office today?
VICTOR: No I am going to be out now because I'm resolving something else in the permit office; finishin
up another contract for another client here in Santurce, at a restaurant but I have to go to the San Juan
Municipal Building at it's 3:00 now so I don't think I'll have time. I can however see you later on within an
hour and hour and half.

Body:
ARLEEN and JUAN VALDEZ a/k/a MORENO to GRACE
ARLEEN and GRACE discuss the art work that Gustavo is supposed to do on the flyers. GRACE says
Gustavo said he was going to do the art work for ARLEEN but not the frames. ARLEEN says he is not
the only one doing art work, that she called him several times yesterday to see if they were going to be
ready, and he had said yes.
[Minimization start -11:27:54 - Minimization end -11:28:30]
ARLEEN tells GRACE that Gustavo told her that she has a lot of money. ARLEEN says that she is not
going to die if he tells her the art work is not ready.
GRACE advices ARLEEN to express herself a more proper way since she is now a business woman,
also be successful in her new career with other clients. ARLEEN says it is not the same thing because
she was taken for a fool by Gustavo, and it upsets her very much.
[Minimization start -11:30:20 - Minimization end -11:30:53]
They continue social conversation regarding the art work by Gustavo.
GRACE asks ARLEEN her whereabouts. ARLEEN says she is at home about to head out.
ARLEEN says that the way she feels right now if she was to catch Gustavo, she will shoot him in the face
about 30 times because she swears to God she is not going to get away with it, that it is not going to be
now but it could be in a or two year or what ever time goes by. ARLEEN says Gustavo will know who she
really is. ARLEEN says she has plenty of money to pay whatever amount they will charge her.
ARLEEN says Moreno is going over there to speak to him (Gustavo).
MORENO: [Background: I heard everything he said last night. I'm going over there, and he better
not tell me that it is not ready. I'm going to tell him.]
ARLEEN: Today I woke up very upset. Moreno is upset. I had the speaker phone on all the time. Moreno
heard all the shit he had said. He (Gustavo) should've told me from the beginning.
een
Social conversation about Gustavo wasting ARLEEN'S time, that she could've looked for someone else's
service.
GRACE advices ARLEEN to take things easy because she is a business woman now and that will ruin
her reputation as such.
MORENO: GRACE, do me a favor, because I know ARLEEN is very upset. Yesterday I heard his
entire conversation. Do me a favor, tell him... I ma going over there now. I'm going to get dressed. He
promised something to ARLEEN, and I am going over there. It's not about the person having money,
what matter is the responsibility. I know ARLEEN. I don't want ARLEEN to go over there because
anything can happen if she and I go. Tell him that I am going to go in person, because he is a man and so
am I. And tell him that I heard the entire conversation and the promise he made to ARLEEN over the
phone. I need that art. So I am going over there and I am going to sit down right over there. Also tell him
that I want him to go with me to the business place so he can see the sign because I noticed something.
That's it. No offense, but he has to do that art for me. So I am going over there now.
GRACE: While you get dressed... I'm almost done having lunch, so I ll go down there in a little bit.
MORENO: Do me that favor. I don't know the number, nor I'm going to talk over the phone. I'm
going over there, he is going to get in his car, I'm going to get in mine so he can see the work he did for
me. It's not about the person having money, but the person has to be responsible. He is a gentleman
and I am gentleman too. He is going to do me that huge favor without fighting or anything. It's me, not
ARLEEN. I'm the person that's going there. I have to leave to New York, so he has to do me those flyers
because he promised them for today... the art work. I want my art. I'll go anywhere. There are more than
enough printing shops in Puerto Rico, and I have more than enough friends in the printing business. Do
me that favor and speak to him, that's it. It's me, not ARLEEN. Me; JUAN VALDEZ. Alright?
GRACE: Alright.
MORENO: I'm the one that's going.
GRACE: Okay.
[End of Call]

ARLEEN: Good afternoon.

BERNAL: Hello.
VALDEZ: Hello.
BERNAL: What is going on?
VALDEZ: Everything is fine. I am over here dropping off the deposition for the case.
BERNAL: I did not want to call you from my telephones. I am calling you from an agency [Referring to a
phone bank] because we do now know what MANNY has told them. That they don't do... they don't put...
the hooks [Phonetically] ...
[Voices Overlap]
VALDEZ: I was going to tell you to take it easy because... I... when they... they keep those cars.They
would have kept the cars if they would have been interested in them. You understand? They keep the cars
in order to searched them thoroughly. You understand? They check the transmission, they look to see
who was the last owner. Everything.
BERNAL: I called you to the other phone.
[Voices Overlap]
VALDEZ: Yes I know.
BERNAL: Here at 138th and Brown Place [Bronx, NY]. I called you from here.
[Voices Overlap]
VALDEZ: [Unintelligible].
BERNAL: This is what we are going to do when you get here. You are going to call me to the base
[dispatcher] and say; 'Ask 9-8 when can he come pick-up...' Lets say Bronco.
VALDEZ: What should I say?
BERNAL: You tell him, 'Bronco at 184th.' I will know more or less.
VALDEZ: Okay. Do not hang-up 9-8. [Pause] All right. You know what leave the car keys for me at Fior's

een

VALDEZ: Yes, okay.
BERNAL: You understand? Because like that... We protect one another.
VALDEZ: It is best to do it like that.
BERNAL: Listen! This girl...
[Voices overlap]
VALDEZ: Have you found out anything about him?
BERNAL: I haven't found out anything because I am not going to ask. The problem is that I do not know
too many people there and I do not want to go around asking anyone anything. I am waiting for the word to

BERNAL: Yes of course I am working. I have to work.

BERNAL: No, no, no, nothing. Everything is quiet. Listen this woman... so and so [Marlene] landlady... I

VALDEZ: I have the money. I will take care of the landlady when I get there tomorrow. What was I going
